IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROMOTE THE WELL-BEING OF ALL PEOPLE OF SOUTHERN NEW MEXICO THROUGH COMMUNITY HEALTH AND SOCIAL SERVICES AND PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE QUALITY PRIMARY MEDICAL, DENTAL, SOCIAL SERVICES AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE AND SERVICES TO LOW-INCOME, UNDERSERVED RESIDENTS OF DONA ANA COUNTY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: LCDF EMPOWERS AND ENRICHES FAMILIES, INDIVIDUALS AND COMMUNITIES BY PROVIDING QUALITY MEDICAL, DENTAL, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH AND EDUCATIONAL SERVICES FOR PEOPLE OF ALL CULTURES.
IRS990.Desc: THE CLINICAL PROGRAM PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE, QUALITY PRIMARY MEDICAL, DENTAL, SOCIAL SERVICES AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE AND SERVICES TO RESIDENTS OF SOUTHERN NEW MEXICO. DURING THE YEAR, 245,238 CLINIC VISITS WERE PERFORMED.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: EARLY HEAD START IS A FEDERAL CHILD-DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM THAT EMPHASIZES FAMILY ENGAGEMENT IN EARLY CHILDHOOD DEVELOPMENT AND EDUCATION. DURING THE YEAR, 246 PARTICIPANTS WERE ENROLLED IN EITHER CENTER-BASED OR HOME-BASED PROGRAMS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HUMAN RESOURCES PERFORMS AN EXTENSIVE WAGE AND SALARY SURVEY AND COMPARISON WITH SIMILAR COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS. COMPARABLE SALARIES AT THE NEW MEXICO DEPARTMENT OF WORKFORCE SOLUTIONS, THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS, AND THE NEW MEXICO PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION ARE IDENTIFIED AND UTILIZED IN DETERMINING WAGE RATES FOR EMPLOYEES AND MANAGEMENT. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS AND APPROVES WAGE CHANGES FOR MANAGEMENT AND KEY EMPLOYEES.
